## Deployment

### Production Backend (Render)
- **URL**: https://sahabnote.onrender.com
- **Health Check**: https://sahabnote.onrender.com/api/health
- **API Docs**: https://sahabnote.onrender.com/docs
- The free tier spins down after 15 min of inactivity; first request may take 30-60s to wake up.
- Data is stored in SQLite on Render's ephemeral filesystem — for production use with persistent data, switch to PostgreSQL.

### Local Development Backend
```bash
./start_backend.sh   # Installs deps and starts FastAPI server on http://localhost:8000
```

## Tested On
- Expo Go SDK 54
- Android (via Expo Go)
- Web (Chrome)

## Client Configuration

All clients (Chrome Extension, Android app, Desktop) need two settings:
1. **Server URL**: For production use `https://sahabnote.onrender.com`; for local dev use `http://localhost:8000` (or your LAN IP for testing on phone)
2. **Auth Token / Sync Key**: Use the sync key obtained from registering/logging in via any client (shared across all clients for the same user account)

### Sync Key for user "etters" (production)
```
sn_f9480efa28b70b6bb18885ea09f82c93ed09a6c7d7e6a3c7
```
Register a new user on any client to get a new sync key.

## Health Monitoring Scripts
- `scripts/health_tray.py` — Linux system tray indicator that pings `https://sahabnote.onrender.com/api/health`
- `scripts/health-widget.html` — Browser-based health widget (open in any browser) that monitors the same endpoint
- Both check every 30 seconds and show green (online) / red (offline) status

